Data Definition Language 
CREATE allows you to create the container for your data. 
used to create tables. You need to define the data type for each column 

DATA TYPES 

1, NUMERIC 
INT integer, whole number only 
(counting clicks, impressions, total leads)

DECIMAL/NUMERIC   exact numbers with decimals
(budgets, revenue)

FLOAT/REAL  approximate numbers with decimals
(calculating complex ratios like CTR, CVR)

2, STRING/TEXT 

VARCHAR(n) variable lenght character 
(campaign names, email addresses, names, 
NVARCHAR national variable characters for any global languages

CHAR(n) fixed-length text for country code or currency code

TEXT for long strings 
(reviews, blog posts)
3, DATE/TIME
DATE for dates yyyy-mm-dd
(start and end dates)
TIMESTAMP/DATETIME stores date and time
(attribution to know when an ad was clicked)
BOOLEAN stores only true or false
(opt in, status or customer is a 'VIP'


